title.undefined: Circular Economy Ontology Network (CEON) - Product Module

description.undefined: The Product module of CEON (Circular Economy Ontology Network).

coversRequirements.value: In addition to requirements covered by imported ODPs, covers the following requirements from Onto-DESIDE D3.1: CVN-Resource-2, CVN-ResrouceType-4, C11-2, C12-1, C13-3, E2-1, T8-3.
In addition to requirements covered by imported ODPs, covers the following requirements from Onto-DESIDE D3.2: CE5-2, C11-2, C12-1, C13-3, E2-1, T8-3.

title.value: Circular Economy Ontology Network (CEON) - Product Module

comment.undefined: The location of supplier of a product or item.
The rules or restrictions made or maintained by authorities.
The generic relation representing the particpation of a resource in some relation. For example, it can be specialized to represent a reified version of an object or data property.

comment.en: A product composition is the composed information of a product in terms of a specific component, in which such a component is also a matter.

comment.undefined: The origin location of a physical object

The relation involving the role of a certain actor with respect to a certain resource, e.g. an organisation or individual (actor) owning (role) a specific product (resource) at a specific point or period in time.

The relation involving the role of a certain actor with respect to a value network or a process in such a network, e.g. an organisation (actor) acting as the recycler (role) in a glass recycling value netowrk (network) at a specific point or period in time. Or an organisation (actor) acting as the dismantler (role) in a dismantling step of a building deconstruction process (process step) at a specific point or period in time.

comment.en: Product or service, or a combination thereof, that fulfils a need of an interested party.

comment.undefined: Something that the actor is capable of doing, e.g. perfomring a certain role in a process, based on some properties, such as access to infrastructure, resources and know-how.

comment.en: Information is an abstract concept that represents any kind of interpretations. For instance, information can be data generated by software systems or data used by people for communications.

comment.undefined: The characteristics or attribuets of a resource.
An infrastructure refers to facilities, services, or systems for participations to function.

comment.en: A matter is a physical substance.

comment.undefined: The location where a physical object is manufactured.
The production location of a physical object

comment.en: Asset from which a solution is created or implemented. Depending on the context, reference to “resource” includes “raw material”, “feedstock”, “material” or “component”. Resource includes any energy type (e.g. the energy content or energy potential of materials). Note 4 to entry: Resources can be considered concerning both stocks and flows.
A physical object is a collection of matter.

comment.undefined: An agent able to act in the context of a circular value network, e.g. an organisation, person.
Represents that something is compliant with some standard or has a received a certain certification.
Resource quality is derived based on assessments of resources considering the conditions and properties.

comment.en: A constituent is a component of object.

comment.undefined: Represents the participation of objects in some situation.
A digital object, e.g. a computer file, that is located on some server, hard drive, or on the web. Most often the digital object is the realization of some piece of information.

comment.en: A product composition is the composed information of a product in terms of a specific component, in which such a component is also a product.

comment.undefined: The location where a physical object is assembled.

comment.en: A set of objects is a set of physical objects (items) that can be of different types, i.e. different kinds of items.

An item is a physical object put into a market for sale, i.e. corresponding to an individual of a product. The item can be a thing that grows naturally or produced through some chemical or manufacturing processes.

comment.undefined: A product object composition is the composed information of a product object in terms of a specific component, in which such a component is also a product object.

comment.en: A batch of objects is a collection of physical objects that are of the same type, e.g. a set of items (product instances) adhering to the same product model.
Represents the common sense notion of a product, i.e. the abstract notion of a product type, which is a model that is used for manufacturing items of that product.

comment.undefined: A collaboration between a set of actors.
The type of an actor, e.g. the type of company, or a specific subtype based on the organisations capabilities.

definition.value: A coherent set of direct positions in space. The positions are held within a Spatial Reference System (SRS).

comment.undefined: A role that an actor can take in a specific context. Applies both to roles in the context of resources, such as owner, manufacturer, reseller etc. of that resource, as well as roles in relation to a circular value network, such as recycler, dismantler, transporter etc., in relation to a material flow.
